OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1780081925
OL,3,CAirport trial judge referred Nigel
OL,4,CFarage comments to Attorney General
OL,6,FHe said he continued to have
OL,7,F"confidence" in the jury to consider
OL,8,Fthe case impartially.
OL,10,FLater in a written ruling, he said: "I
OL,11,Ftook the view that the observation
OL,12,Fmade by Nigel Farage was potentially a
OL,13,Fcontempt of court as it implied the
OL,14,Fguilt of the defendants.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@LO]rD@eOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
