OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1780081925
OL,3,CAirport trial judge referred Nigel
OL,4,CFarage comments to Attorney General
OL,6,F"As Nigel Farage is a well-known
OL,7,Fpolitician with a considerable
OL,8,Ffollowing and whose public utterances
OL,9,Fattract a lot of attention, I decided
OL,10,Fto refer the matter to the Attorney
OL,11,FGeneral so that he could consider
OL,12,Fwhether there should be a prosecution
OL,13,Ffor contempt of court.
OL,15,F"That matter is now out of my hands."
OL,17,FHe added: "It was also necessary for
OL,18,Fme to consider whether this
OL,19,Fdevelopment had the potential to
OL,20,Faffect the fairness of the trial
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@AOUwD@eO]yD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
