OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,393,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F392A1780081925
OL,3,CAirport trial judge referred Nigel
OL,4,CFarage comments to Attorney General
OL,6,F"I decided that this intervention,
OL,7,Fhowever unwelcome, would not adversely
OL,8,Faffect the fairness of the trial."
OL,10,FThe Attorney General's Office has
OL,11,Fsince confirmed that law officers have
OL,12,Fnot issued contempt proceedings in the
OL,13,Fcase.
OL,15,FThe Attorney General can bring
OL,16,Fproceedings for contempt of court
OL,17,Fagainst anyone who prejudices or
OL,18,Fobstructs the administration of
OL,19,Fjustice, or creates a real risk of
OL,20,Fthat happening.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@bO]
